(PLUS UP TO $3,600 Open ATB) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $10,000 OR LESS SINCE JUNE 17, 2021 OR CLAIMING PRICE $20,000. RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOOTSIE'S GALAXY chased the pace while three wide down the first quarter, was moving up on the turn to challenge for the lead with inner rivals, was menacing gamely down the lane and was up at the wire to prove best. GOOD SCOUT dueled for the lead with an inner rival down the stretch and into the turn, then battled between rivals down the early stretch, continued to dig in grudgingly but hung in the end. PUNCH EM dueled for the lead from the inside into the turn, then vied with outer rivals heading into the stretch, menaced gamely but hung in the end and was best for show. SWEET RIVER BAINES chased the pace from the inside, then bid on the turn to rally in late stretch but it was too little too late. IMA BLING CAT chased the pace while two wide, then moved up to vie for the lead leaving the turn and into the stretch, was used up and gave way late. PALATIAL TIMES raced behind the field then bid from the inside on the turn came out six wide in the stretch and was no threat.

CAPETOWN CANDY trailed throughout and was no factor. There was a JOCKEY'S OBJECTION, the rider of DRENCHED claimed foul against the rider of BASKET CASE for interference in the home stretch.
